01:03:27.760 --> 01:03:31.360
I just want to stress one thing
that I do believe is interesting

01:03:31.360 --> 01:03:34.910
for at least our starting
point when we started.

01:03:34.910 --> 01:03:37.540
Every order goes for crisis
and being changed and so

01:03:37.540 --> 01:03:39.780
from this point there is
nothing that is happening

01:03:39.780 --> 01:03:42.580
that is historic than expected.

01:03:42.580 --> 01:03:46.970
But if you go back to 1989,
1990s the major story was

01:03:46.970 --> 01:03:49.530
that this was a kind
of a world order

01:03:49.530 --> 01:03:52.980
which everybody is going
to feel victorious.

01:03:52.980 --> 01:03:56.580
And though on the level of
the rhetoric it is not simply

01:03:56.580 --> 01:03:59.200
that the West has
won the cold war,

01:03:59.200 --> 01:04:01.710
that the Russian people
has won the cold war

01:04:01.710 --> 01:04:04.810
against the communist regime
and everybody was winning.

01:04:04.810 --> 01:04:08.890
Thirty years later everybody
identified as a victim

01:04:08.890 --> 01:04:12.980
and loser, Russia to be honest
is the most obvious case,

01:04:12.980 --> 01:04:15.490
but then you go into central and
eastern Europe particularly some

01:04:15.490 --> 01:04:19.050
of the populist government who
said we lost, and then suddenly

01:04:19.050 --> 01:04:21.560
with President Trump the
Americans said we are the

01:04:21.560 --> 01:04:26.020
biggest victim of the world that
the American created in 1989.

01:04:26.020 --> 01:04:29.150
And for me this type of an
important transformation

01:04:29.150 --> 01:04:31.330
of the world which was a win-win

01:04:31.330 --> 01:04:35.880
and now is lose-lose is
something to be taken seriously

01:04:35.880 --> 01:04:38.900
because it is also trying
to throw not simply a kind

01:04:38.900 --> 01:04:40.940
of a language, but
this is something

01:04:40.940 --> 01:04:42.350
that Simon Vale [assumed
spelling] is going

01:04:42.350 --> 01:04:46.750
to define cheap collective
imagination.

01:04:46.750 --> 01:04:50.430
Suddenly you start to see the
world totally differently.

01:04:50.430 --> 01:04:52.430
Something that till
yesterday was looking

01:04:52.430 --> 01:04:56.540
as an advantage starts to see
as disadvantage, vulnerability.

01:04:56.540 --> 01:04:57.960
We are finishing the book

01:04:57.960 --> 01:04:59.560
with Steven Hobbs [assumed
spelling] this was the reason I

01:04:59.560 --> 01:05:03.120
was here, I'll give just one
example, English language.

01:05:03.120 --> 01:05:06.960
Fifteen years ago everybody is
going to claim that the spread

01:05:06.960 --> 01:05:10.100
of the English language
was the best demonstration

01:05:10.100 --> 01:05:12.040
of the American soft power.

01:05:12.040 --> 01:05:13.510
You go everywhere
and you're going

01:05:13.510 --> 01:05:15.680
to hear somebody
speaking English.

01:05:15.680 --> 01:05:19.370
And then suddenly the spread
of the English language starts

01:05:19.370 --> 01:05:21.740
to be perceived as
America's vulnerability.

01:05:21.740 --> 01:05:24.930
Why? I'm just going to
give you three examples.

01:05:24.930 --> 01:05:28.840
Because if everybody speaks
English everybody knows how

01:05:28.840 --> 01:05:32.950
America functions, but America
is not very aware how other

01:05:32.950 --> 01:05:34.480
people function.

01:05:34.480 --> 01:05:38.420
It is easier for everybody to go
onto social media and to pretend

01:05:38.420 --> 01:05:41.760
to be an American, it is not
easy for the Americans to go

01:05:41.760 --> 01:05:45.420
onto social media and to
pretend being Bulgarians.

01:05:45.420 --> 01:05:48.100
Secondly, on the level of
knowledge the fact that you have

01:05:48.100 --> 01:05:51.590
so many English speakers
in different countries,

01:05:51.590 --> 01:05:54.320
you go to a country you're
always going to find somebody

01:05:54.320 --> 01:05:56.960
who speaks English and you
have the feeling that you talk

01:05:56.960 --> 01:05:59.440
to the local population.

01:05:59.440 --> 01:06:01.790
But not always the
English speakers

01:06:01.790 --> 01:06:05.080
which are self-selected groups
are very much representatives

01:06:05.080 --> 01:06:06.860
for the general kind
of understanding

01:06:06.860 --> 01:06:09.040
in the very general
mode of the country.

01:06:09.040 --> 01:06:14.410
So certainly, strangely enough,
which was America's biggest kind

01:06:14.410 --> 01:06:18.500
of advantage starts to be
perceived asymmetry, vulnerable,

01:06:18.500 --> 01:06:22.200
everybody can interfere in our
politics and we find it more

01:06:22.200 --> 01:06:24.540
and more difficult to interfere
in the politics of others

01:06:24.540 --> 01:06:26.510
because we don't know
what is going on.

01:06:26.510 --> 01:06:29.650
This type of change is for
me critically important.

01:06:29.650 --> 01:06:32.470
Something that you liked
yesterday you start

01:06:32.470 --> 01:06:33.790
to fear today.

01:06:33.790 --> 01:06:35.840
