This is a comment, but
feel free to comment

01:08:21.350 --> 01:08:23.050
on the comment, if you would.

01:08:23.050 --> 01:08:27.500
I think hypocrisy is a very
interesting conceptual way

01:08:27.500 --> 01:08:31.440
to look at it, particularly
when it's Putin versus the West

01:08:31.440 --> 01:08:37.790
or whatever, but from an
internal Western perspective I

01:08:37.790 --> 01:08:40.920
think a useful way to
look at it is laziness.

01:08:40.920 --> 01:08:47.980
I think it strikes me how
lazy the elites of the West

01:08:47.980 --> 01:08:53.510
who talk endlessly about this
liberal international order how

01:08:53.510 --> 01:08:55.490
sort of lack of effort
they've put

01:08:55.490 --> 01:08:58.620
into even understanding
what creating

01:08:58.620 --> 01:09:00.120
and maintaining that order was.

01:09:00.120 --> 01:09:04.270
I mean I just, I could give many
examples, but I'd just give one.

01:09:04.270 --> 01:09:08.710
The Bretton Wood system,
you have to read article

01:09:08.710 --> 01:09:12.600
after article after article in
which Eikenberry and others go

01:09:12.600 --> 01:09:15.450
on and on and on about
the alphabet soup

01:09:15.450 --> 01:09:18.870
of the Bretton Wood system.

01:09:18.870 --> 01:09:24.500
How hard people like the
young Paul Volker used to work

01:09:24.500 --> 01:09:29.330
to maintain the convertibility
of the dollar into gold

01:09:29.330 --> 01:09:34.700
at $35 an ounce and not keep the
whole system from crashing down,

01:09:34.700 --> 01:09:38.940
and it was just really
hard work.

01:09:38.940 --> 01:09:43.560
Now Germany runs a $300
billion trade surplus,

01:09:43.560 --> 01:09:47.290
the US runs a $500
billion trade deficit,

01:09:47.290 --> 01:09:49.020
it goes on and on and on.

01:09:49.020 --> 01:09:54.030
The IMF is a bunch of well-paid
bureaucrats who give advice

01:09:54.030 --> 01:09:56.740
to mostly developing countries
and occasionally a country

01:09:56.740 --> 01:10:00.870
like Greece, but there's no
really hard work that goes

01:10:00.870 --> 01:10:06.210
into maintaining a
difficult costly world order.

01:10:06.210 --> 01:10:09.440
And so what we've simultaneously
done is put less and less effort

01:10:09.440 --> 01:10:13.210
into maintaining that order and
made it more and more expansive,

01:10:13.210 --> 01:10:16.170
both geographically it's
supposed to apply to everybody,

01:10:16.170 --> 01:10:20.210
everybody except a few rogues,
to use the lingo of the '90s,

01:10:20.210 --> 01:10:23.660
and also more and more areas
in our national criminal court,

01:10:23.660 --> 01:10:24.960
Kyoto and so on and so forth.

01:10:24.960 --> 01:10:29.800
So there's a kind
of a now a laziness,

01:10:29.800 --> 01:10:31.510
we invoke the international
order

01:10:31.510 --> 01:10:33.310
but we don't put
much effort into it.

01:10:33.310 --> 01:10:37.080
Now the cold war, of
course, imposed discipline,

01:10:37.080 --> 01:10:40.300
it was partly if
the dollar goes,

01:10:40.300 --> 01:10:43.610
if we go off the gold standard
or whatever the world is going

01:10:43.610 --> 01:10:45.670
to come to an end that's
what people like Johnson

01:10:45.670 --> 01:10:47.090
and Eisenhower thought
and so on.

01:10:47.090 --> 01:10:53.120
So the East-West conflict
imposed a discipline,

01:10:53.120 --> 01:10:55.750
maybe it was just a
different sociology and so on,

01:10:55.750 --> 01:11:00.060
but I do think we have a
problem not only with hypocrisy

01:11:00.060 --> 01:11:01.770
but also with kind of effort.

01:11:01.770 --> 01:11:04.940
And the European Union
is a wonderful thing,

01:11:04.940 --> 01:11:09.190
but it does kind of
and enlargement cost

01:11:09.190 --> 01:11:11.670
and it was not cheap and
so on, but it does kind

01:11:11.670 --> 01:11:14.420
of spin-out lots and
lots and lots of projects

01:11:14.420 --> 01:11:17.220
that sound great, but
how much real effort goes

01:11:17.220 --> 01:11:18.520
into actually reality.

01:11:18.520 --> 01:11:20.980
Anyway, that's a comment,
but I would like anybody

01:11:20.980 --> 01:11:23.380
to comment on it, as well.

